most cases, recovery is rapid after GI foreign body removal, and ferrets are able to eat soft foods within 12 hours after surgery. Most ferrets can be discharged within 48 hours after surgery. Prevention of foreign body obstructions includes recommending the regular use of a hairball laxative preparation during active shedding seasons and "ferret-proofing" the household. Ferrets should not be left uncaged or unsupervised. Advise owners to avoid giving small rubber "squeak" toys to pet ferrets and remove soft rubber objects (e.g., rubber-soled shoes and earphones) from the ferret's accessible environment. 


